-- Arab Bank Appeals Judge's Sanctions in Case Accusing Bank of Terrorist Aid
-- B y   D o n   J e f f r e y
-- 2010-11-04T18:35:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/arab-bank-appeals-judge-s-sanctions-in-case-accusing-bank-of-terrorist-aid.html
Arab Bank Plc, which was accused by
American victims of terrorist attacks in Israel of providing
financial aid to suicide bombers’ families, is appealing a
judge’s sanctions for not turning over some bank account
records, according to a court filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donald Jeffrey in New York at 
